---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Modal from '../../components/Modal.astro';
---
<BaseLayout title="Ancient Sophistication" description="The mathematics of quasicrystals in Islamic architecture.">

    <header class="text-center my-12 md:my-16">
        <p class="font-semibold text-blue-600 dark:text-blue-400">Interactive Report</p>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100 tracking-tight mt-2">
            Ancient Sophistication
        </h1>
    </header>

    <!-- Main Introduction Section -->
    <section id="introduction" class="text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold dark:text-slate-200">An Integration of Knowledge</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-gray-600 dark:text-slate-300">
            This exploration demonstrates that historical "secrets" are profound insights into reality, articulated through the tools of the time. The mathematical genius in Islamic patterns represents a sophisticated, intuitive grasp of complex phenomena, achieved without modern computers and challenging a linear view of scientific progress.
        </p>
    </section>

    <!-- Three-Card Layout -->
    <section class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 my-16 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border dark:border-slate-700 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3 text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">Ancient Mathematical Wisdom</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                Islamic architecture is not just aesthetically beautiful; it's a library of advanced mathematical concepts, specifically non-repeating patterns that exhibit long-range order, known as quasicrystals.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border dark:border-slate-700 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3 text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">Artisans as Pioneers</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                Without computational aids, artisans used tools like "Girih tiles" and geometric rules to create stunningly complex designs, demonstrating a deep, intuitive understanding of non-periodic mathematics.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-slate-800 p-6 rounded-lg shadow-md border dark:border-slate-700 hover:shadow-xl hover:-translate-y-1 transition-all duration-300">
            <h3 class="font-bold text-xl mb-3 text-gray-900 dark:text-slate-100">A Different Way of Seeing</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 dark:text-slate-300">
                Engaging with these intricate patterns fostered a cognitive framework open to seeing hidden structuresâ€”a way of thinking that resonates with the challenges of understanding quantum-level phenomena today.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Button to trigger the modal -->
    <div class="text-center">
         <button
            type="button"
            data-modal-toggle="research-modal"
            class="bg-blue-600 text-white font-semibold px-6 py-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 dark:bg-blue-500 dark:hover:bg-blue-600 transition-transform hover:scale-105"
        >
            <i class="fas fa-scroll mr-2"></i> View Full Research Text
        </button>
    </div>


    <!-- Modal for the Full Research Text -->
    <Modal modalId="research-modal" title="Full Research: Unveiling Ancient Sophistication">
        <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none">
            <!-- You can paste the entire, unformatted text from your research document here -->
            <p>This is where the full, detailed text from the research document would go. It can be as long as needed, as it will have its own scrollbar, keeping the main page clean and focused.</p>
            <p>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipiscing elit. Sed non risus. Suspendisse lectus tortor, dignissim sit amet, adipiscing nec, ultricies sed, dolor. Cras elementum ultrices diam. Maecenas ligula massa, varius a, semper congue, euismod non, mi.</p>
        </div>
    </Modal>

</BaseLayout>
